11:27.821 --> 11:29.354
Well...
- Jess, I'm crazy about you.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.723
Ryan, look. Oh, God,
it's so complicated.

11:31.725 --> 11:33.825
Can I just put some pants on
when we talk about this?

11:33.827 --> 11:35.326
It is complicated.

11:35.328 --> 11:37.896
This would have been worth it.

11:37.898 --> 11:39.731
Oh, God. Ryan. Ryan!

11:39.733 --> 11:41.166
Oh, God!

11:41.168 --> 11:42.567
NICK:
Oh! Yeah!

11:42.569 --> 11:44.703
(hooting, whooping
and overlapping chatter)

11:44.705 --> 11:47.405
SCHMIDT:
Oh, no!

11:47.407 --> 11:50.041
Freaking Bangsgiving.

11:53.579 --> 11:56.114
SCHMIDT:
No, I actually put those
in there myself.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.317
I'll tell you, I wouldn't
eat asparagus though.

11:59.319 --> 12:00.518
It makes your pee smell.

12:00.520 --> 12:01.453
(laughs)
- Mmm.

12:03.856 --> 12:06.725
Hey, Cece, I got
that $20 I owe you.

12:06.727 --> 12:09.094
It's, uh... it's
in my bedroom.

12:09.096 --> 12:11.529
Okay.

12:11.531 --> 12:13.598
Yeah, it's right this way.

12:17.870 --> 12:21.239
You're really
sexy for a Jew.

12:21.241 --> 12:23.675
Not now, woman!

12:23.677 --> 12:25.677
Wait. What?

12:25.679 --> 12:28.012
Who needs men?
You don't need a man.

12:28.014 --> 12:30.248
You can lift your
own furniture.
- Hey, Pepper.

12:30.250 --> 12:33.118
Oh, God.
- Oh, my God,
are you okay?

12:33.120 --> 12:36.688
I am so sorry.
You approached my blind spot.
(Coach groans)

12:36.690 --> 12:39.057
Your money's in here somewhere.
Let me just find it, okay?
Oh, great.

12:39.059 --> 12:40.959
<i>Oh!</i>

12:40.961 --> 12:42.427
What's wrong? You hurt yourself?

12:42.429 --> 12:44.295
No. It's just not there.
Uh, let me.

12:44.297 --> 12:45.797
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh!

12:45.799 --> 12:47.398
Ooh. Ooh,
that feels so good!

12:47.400 --> 12:49.734
When I'm looking for your money,
it feels so good.

12:49.736 --> 12:52.437
(laughing):
Oh! I love that!

12:52.439 --> 12:54.205
You're a nasty woman!

12:54.207 --> 12:55.940
'Cause you're making me
give the money to you.

12:55.942 --> 12:57.375
Nick...

12:57.377 --> 12:59.544
Oh, Cece, you love this!
Getting your money.

12:59.546 --> 13:02.046
What exactly are you
doing right now?
- (whispers):
I'm getting your money.

13:02.048 --> 13:03.448
You're definitely
not getting my money.

13:03.450 --> 13:04.949
In no world
do you have my money.

13:04.951 --> 13:06.584
I was flirting with you

13:06.586 --> 13:08.653
to give Schmidt a taste
of his own medicine.

13:08.655 --> 13:10.288
Okay? And it's a huge mistake,

13:10.290 --> 13:11.923
and insulting to everyone
involved, and I'm sorry.

13:11.925 --> 13:13.424
Yeah, and also, he would never

13:13.426 --> 13:15.226
fall for that at all, okay?

13:15.228 --> 13:16.995
You're a dead man,
Miller!

13:16.997 --> 13:18.296
Don't. Don't.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.430
SCHMIDT:
I'll choke you to death.

13:19.432 --> 13:20.732
I'll choke<i> you</i> to death.

13:20.734 --> 13:22.267
CECE:
Barely fighting.

13:22.269 --> 13:23.568
Schmidt, nothing was going on!

13:23.570 --> 13:24.803
He was just trying
to make you jealous.

13:24.805 --> 13:26.437
Please. I know that!

13:26.439 --> 13:28.740
He would never hit on you.
You're on my Never List.

13:28.742 --> 13:32.177
I know she's on your Never...
Whoa! Whoa! What are you doing?

13:32.179 --> 13:34.512
You're pissed at me for bringing
Lucy, and you bring Tran

13:34.514 --> 13:36.648
as a date?
Hey, leave Tran out of this.
He fought in Korea!

13:36.650 --> 13:38.817
I don't know which side,
but I know he's a war hero.

13:38.819 --> 13:40.251
You couldn't find one of
those drunk girls at the bar?

13:40.253 --> 13:41.452
The ones with no
family or friends?

13:41.454 --> 13:43.021
That's your sweet spot, man.

13:43.023 --> 13:45.490
I know I could have.
I didn't want to.
- Why not?

13:46.692 --> 13:48.293
What kind of woman
have you been sleeping with

13:48.295 --> 13:49.727
since you and Jess broke up?

13:50.696 --> 13:52.931
Terrible ones.

13:52.933 --> 13:54.699
And how does that make you feel?

13:54.701 --> 13:56.601
Terrible.

13:56.603 --> 13:58.303
Then really good.

13:58.305 --> 14:00.271
Expected. Expected.

14:00.273 --> 14:02.106
There you go.
- But then,
immediately after, terrible.

14:02.108 --> 14:03.942
I'm just gonna put this
out there, but I think

14:03.944 --> 14:05.443
you'd probably rather like
to sleep with someone

14:05.445 --> 14:07.145
who doesn't make you feel
terrible,

14:07.147 --> 14:10.248
but you're just a little
afraid of getting hurt again.

14:11.383 --> 14:13.585
No, that doesn't sound right.

14:15.287 --> 14:17.222
You know, growing up,

14:17.224 --> 14:19.357
we had this lunch lady
named Ms. Witten.

14:19.359 --> 14:22.393
One day, I cut in line so
I can get extra Tater Tots,

14:22.395 --> 14:25.163
and as punishment, she
made me eat the entire tray

14:25.165 --> 14:27.065
in front of her...

14:27.067 --> 14:30.068
while she stared at me
for a long period of time.

14:30.070 --> 14:33.137
I'm not sure if you know how
hard that is for a growing boy.

14:33.139 --> 14:35.406
How old were you?
- I was 18.

14:35.408 --> 14:37.575
(laughs)

14:37.577 --> 14:40.745
If it helps, we're called
lunch monitors now.

14:40.747 --> 14:42.847
No one says
"lunch lady" anymore.

14:42.849 --> 14:47.852
Oh. Kind of like how we can't
call little people "shrinkies."

14:47.854 --> 14:50.622
Oh. Lunch Monitor
Pearl. I like it.

14:56.061 --> 14:58.730
Excellent form.

14:58.732 --> 15:01.099
You don't have a hard job.

15:03.035 --> 15:04.602
So, I saw your
butt earlier.

15:04.604 --> 15:06.371
It's been holding up nicely.

15:06.373 --> 15:08.840
It does the trick.

15:10.843 --> 15:12.844
And I noticed,
uh, Ryan left.

15:12.846 --> 15:16.581
Yeah. Ugh!
It's so embarrassing.

15:16.583 --> 15:18.283
I kind of came onto him,

15:18.285 --> 15:22.453
and he told me
he wanted more than just sex.

15:22.455 --> 15:25.556
He wanted more than sex
and that's a bad thing? How?

15:25.558 --> 15:27.258
Well, look, I'm his boss.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.694
We could get sued,
and I could get fired.

15:29.696 --> 15:31.729
There's a reason
it's against the rules.

15:31.731 --> 15:33.264
You gotta br... okay.

15:33.266 --> 15:34.966
Remember when we tried to watch
<i>Ferris Bueller's Day Off?</i>

15:34.968 --> 15:37.869
Okay, I stick by that--
that kid is not a hero.

15:37.871 --> 15:40.138
All he does is break rules.
What's so great about that?

15:40.140 --> 15:42.874
You're taking Rooney's side.
No one takes Rooney's side.

15:42.876 --> 15:44.475
I'm a vice principal--
Rooney is my people.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.078
Ferris hijacks a parade.

15:47.080 --> 15:48.579
That is an act of terror.

15:48.581 --> 15:50.315
You want to know what I think,
'cause you're not going

15:50.317 --> 15:51.816
to like it.
- What?

15:51.818 --> 15:53.785
I don't think this is
about breaking rules.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.286
I think Ryan scares you.

15:55.288 --> 15:57.822
You like him, and you're
going to have to put yourself

15:57.824 --> 16:00.258
out there again,
and that scares you.

16:00.260 --> 16:02.827
But look,

16:02.829 --> 16:05.897
life moves really fast.

16:05.899 --> 16:10.935
And if you don't stop and
look around once in a while,

16:10.937 --> 16:13.571
you just might miss it.

16:13.573 --> 16:15.840
Is that from<i> Ferris Bueller?</i>

16:15.842 --> 16:17.108
Yes, it is.
- Okay.

16:17.110 --> 16:18.576
It's a terrific movie.
- All right.

16:18.578 --> 16:20.311
And I delivered it perfectly.

16:20.313 --> 16:22.146
It was pretty good.

16:25.851 --> 16:27.452
What are you doing here?

16:27.454 --> 16:29.220
You're fired.

16:30.189 --> 16:32.190
(laughs)
Just kidding.

16:32.192 --> 16:34.158
Oh, God.

16:36.929 --> 16:39.097
You left without eating
so I thought, um...

16:39.099 --> 16:41.265
I'd bring you a pie.
Well, most of a pie.

16:41.267 --> 16:43.301
The guys ate some of it.
That's a lie.

16:43.303 --> 16:46.004
I ate-I ate-I ate a piece
on the way over.

16:46.006 --> 16:47.305
I-I ate two pieces.

16:47.307 --> 16:48.606
Three pieces.

16:48.608 --> 16:50.141
Thank you.

16:50.143 --> 16:51.509
You're welcome.

16:51.511 --> 16:53.711
Would you like to come inside?

16:53.713 --> 16:54.879
No, um, I came here
to say something

16:54.881 --> 16:57.281
and that is...

16:57.283 --> 16:59.350
I want more, too.

17:02.955 --> 17:04.188
This dish is empty.

17:04.190 --> 17:06.958
Okay. I ate the whole pie.

17:06.960 --> 17:08.826
Look, I don't know
what I'm doing

17:08.828 --> 17:10.161
or where this is going

17:10.163 --> 17:13.231
(sighs)
and I'm scared, but...

17:13.233 --> 17:16.401
it's worth it
'cause it feels big.

17:16.403 --> 17:19.404
And that's why I'm going
to leave right now,

17:19.406 --> 17:21.406
and we're going to take it slow.

17:29.081 --> 17:30.681
Wow.

17:30.683 --> 17:33.885
Well, tonight is Bangsgiving,

17:33.887 --> 17:35.887
and I have to honor my
American traditions.

17:35.889 --> 17:38.723
And it's my duty
as an American...

17:41.193 --> 17:44.529
I think I'm going to stop
being afraid and start dating.

17:44.531 --> 17:47.598
You probably knew
all along, didn't you?

17:47.600 --> 17:50.768
If only I could
meet a girl like you, Tran.

17:50.770 --> 17:53.004
Your face, your brain--
throw it in a dress.

17:53.006 --> 17:55.740
Oh, daddy,
I'd be with her forever.

17:55.742 --> 17:57.208
I'm getting off topic.

17:57.210 --> 18:00.011
Thanks for the talk.
I feel a lot better.

18:01.180 --> 18:02.780
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:03.949 --> 18:05.883
Tran, are these all yours?

18:05.885 --> 18:07.418
Come on, man.

18:07.420 --> 18:09.087
I thought you were
switching to white wine.

18:09.089 --> 18:11.089
How do you think you're going
to get home now?

18:11.091 --> 18:13.758
You're not driving, so how are
you going to get home?

18:13.760 --> 18:15.927
(knocking)

18:15.929 --> 18:17.695
Hey.

18:17.697 --> 18:20.031
Are you Nick?

18:20.033 --> 18:24.035
You the guy who's obsessed
with my grandfather?

18:25.270 --> 18:27.705
Grandpaps,
you ready to go?

18:33.378 --> 18:35.780
Hey.
- (screams)

18:35.782 --> 18:38.983
Ah, ah, ha... hey.

18:38.985 --> 18:40.885
I'm taking off. Um...

18:40.887 --> 18:42.553
sorry I body-slammed you

18:42.555 --> 18:44.755
but this doesn't feel like
it's working out

18:44.757 --> 18:46.257
so I don't really want
to waste our time.

18:46.259 --> 18:48.893
Look, Pepper, um...

18:48.895 --> 18:50.161
I think you're beautiful,

18:50.163 --> 18:52.263
and very nice.

18:52.265 --> 18:53.898
I just, uh...

18:53.900 --> 18:56.400
You know, I'm not used to...

18:56.402 --> 18:58.970
dating women that
are stronger than me.

18:58.972 --> 19:01.172
How do you know
that I'm stronger than you?

19:01.174 --> 19:02.940
Do you want to arm wrestle?

19:02.942 --> 19:04.509
Yeah, like I'm that insecure
that I have to prove

19:04.511 --> 19:06.944
my masculinity by
arm wrestling a girl.

19:06.946 --> 19:09.313
(yells)
Come on.

19:09.315 --> 19:10.848
Ready?
- Yeah.

19:10.850 --> 19:12.350
One, two, three.

19:12.352 --> 19:15.753
(grunting)

19:15.755 --> 19:17.955
(yells)

19:17.957 --> 19:20.024
Yes! That's how you do it!

19:20.026 --> 19:23.094
That's how it's
uh-uh-uh done!

19:23.096 --> 19:25.363
(moaning)
- (giggling)

19:26.698 --> 19:28.099
Thank you for
letting me win.

19:28.101 --> 19:29.834
Sure. Anytime.

19:35.974 --> 19:37.308
Well, Lucy left.

19:37.310 --> 19:39.477
Turns out she's a bit
of an anti-Semite.

19:39.479 --> 19:41.946
Hmm.
- Yeah, looks like
we both struck out.

19:41.948 --> 19:43.514
Okay, Schmidt,
there is no Geoff.

19:43.516 --> 19:46.517
Come on. But to honest, I'm
kind of glad there isn't.

19:46.519 --> 19:47.818
You know,
Thanksgiving should be spent

19:47.820 --> 19:49.887
with the people
that you care about.

19:51.223 --> 19:52.857
Let me get you a beer.

19:52.859 --> 19:54.225
By the way...

19:54.227 --> 19:56.194
you're on my Never List, too.

20:03.302 --> 20:05.570
Hi.

20:05.572 --> 20:07.138
Are you Cece?

20:07.140 --> 20:08.906
I'm Geoff.

20:08.908 --> 20:10.174
Um, I'm Schmidt's friend.

20:10.176 --> 20:11.375
I'm sorry I'm late.

20:11.377 --> 20:13.477
I hit a peacock on my way here

20:13.479 --> 20:16.514
and then I held it in my arms
until it died.

20:16.516 --> 20:19.684
It was horrible,
but also kind of uplifting.

20:19.686 --> 20:22.286
Um, anyway,
I brought creamed spinach.

20:24.856 --> 20:27.758
